Package utilities

Class Summary
ErrorEvent ErrorEvent to log errors thrown in the program, in a similar way to Exceptions.
Event Event to provide methods common to subclasses, such as toString.
IllegalArgumentEvent IllegalArgumentEvent to log argument errors thrown in the program, in a similar way to Exceptions.
InformationEvent InformationEvent to log information and significant events which happen during the running of the program.
InformationHighEvent InformationHighEvent to log information of high importance, in a similar way to Exceptions.
InformationLowEvent InformationLowEvent to log information of low importance, in a similar way to Exceptions.
InformationNormEvent InformationNormEvent to log information of normal importance, in a similar way to Exceptions.
IOEvent IOEvent to log IO errors thrown in the program, in a similar way to Exceptions.
Logger Logger to print Event objects to a log file, so the terminal is not needed while the program executes, and significant Events can still be viewed by the user.
TimeEvent ErrorEvent to log the current time since the start of timing, and a message, e.g.
WarningEvent WarningEvent to log potential problems or errors thrown in the program, in a similar way to Exceptions.
